Defer the model_root_dir.exists() precondition until after the
custom-session early-return, so callers that supply their own
onnxruntime InferenceSession (immich-machine-learning, anyone using
PR #451's custom-session adapter) don't trip Path(None) → TypeError.

Upstream regression introduced by RapidOCR commit 8ea96265
("feat(python): add model_root_dir and download_models", 2026-03-19),
which placed the new precondition before the PR #451 short-circuit
that immich-ml depends on. Reported as immich-app/immich#28331; no
upstream fix PR linked at the time of writing.

This patch is the minimal reordering: move the model_root_dir check
to immediately before its first real consumer (the `model_path is
None` block that uses `model_root_dir / ...`). Behaviour for callers
who DO need on-disk models is unchanged.

--- a/rapidocr/inference_engine/onnxruntime/main.py
+++ b/rapidocr/inference_engine/onnxruntime/main.py
@@ -17,10 +17,6 @@ from .provider_config import ProviderConfig

 class OrtInferSession(InferSession):
     def __init__(self, cfg: Dict[str, Any]):
-        model_root_dir = Path(cfg.get("model_root_dir"))
-        if not model_root_dir.exists():
-            raise FileNotFoundError(f"model_root_dir {model_root_dir} does not exist")
-
         # support custom session (PR #451)
         session = cfg.get("session", None)
         if session is not None:
@@ -33,6 +29,10 @@ class OrtInferSession(InferSession):
             self.session = session
             return

+        model_root_dir = Path(cfg.get("model_root_dir"))
+        if not model_root_dir.exists():
+            raise FileNotFoundError(f"model_root_dir {model_root_dir} does not exist")
+
         model_path = cfg.get("model_path", None)
         if model_path is None:
             # 说明用户没有指定自己模型，使用默认模型
